      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 2.5",
      "body" : "It has been my experience that the actual heap size Java will accept using a 32b VM (on a 32b or 64b system -- the VM is the important part, here), is around 2G.   Also, surprised asker did not first search and find: <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/1596009/java-lang-outofmemoryerror-java-heap-space\" title=\"java lang outofmemoryerror java heap space\">stackoverflow.com/questions/1596009/&hellip;</a>  and:  <a href=\"http://stackoverflow.com/questions/37335/how-to-deal-with-java-lang-outofmemoryerror-java-heap-space-error-64mb-heap-s\" title=\"how to deal with java lang outofmemoryerror java heap space error 64mb heap s\">stackoverflow.com/questions/37335/&hellip;</a>"
