    "question_id" : 1565388,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>You can increase to <code>2GB</code> on a <code>32</code> bit system. If you're on a 64 bit system you can go higher. No need to worry if you've chosen incorrectly, if you ask for 5g on a 32 bit system java will complain about an invalid value and quit.</p>\n<p>As others have posted, use the cmd-line flags - e.g.</p>\n<pre><code>java -Xmx6g myprogram\n</code></pre>\n<p>You can get a full list (or a nearly full list, anyway) by typing java -X.</p>\n"
  }, {
